# Cursor rules index

Use this to pick the right rule for the current task.

| Rule | When to use |
|------|-------------|
| `ai-editors-skills-subagents.mdc` | Canonical context (AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md), skills, subagents, multi-editor setup |
| **Project skills** | Reusable workflows: `.cursor/skills/` (git pull with WIP, add native module, before-commit, trading safety, build from clean). See `.cursor/skills/README.md`. |
| **Subagents** | When to use which: docs/SUBAGENTS_REFERENCE.md, .cursor/skills/when-to-use-subagents.md (mcp_task: code-reviewer, trading-reviewer, refactor, test-writer, generalPurpose; exarp-go; Claude agents) |
| `ai-context-standards.mdc` | Map of context files, which rule when, OpenCode/Claude/Cursor commands |
| `just-cmake-shortcuts.mdc` | Prefer Just/CMake commands when suggesting (just build, build:ai-friendly, just pre-push, just tag-ok, git:pull-safe, r for repo root; proto C++ at build) |
| `documentation.mdc` | @docs usage, global docs, API/architecture references (auto when editing `docs/**/*.md`) |
| `hooks.mdc` | Git hooks (pre-commit, docs validation), exarp-go setup_hooks |
| `project-automation.mdc` | exarp-go MCP tools, docs health, Todo2 alignment, security scanning |
| `automation-tool-suggestions.mdc` | When to suggest automation tools (context-aware) |
| `todo2.mdc` | Todo2 workflow (create_todos, research, review, refinement) |
| `cpp-source.mdc` | Editing C++ source/headers (`native/src/**`, `native/include/**`) |
| `cpp-tests.mdc` | Editing C++ tests (`native/tests/**`) |
| `python-code.mdc` | Editing Python (`python/**`) |
| `semgrep.mdc` | Before generating code; security_check |
| `ollama.mdc` | Privacy-sensitive code analysis (trading logic, risk) |
| `context7.mdc` | Library/docs lookups; append "use context7" to prompts |
| `notebooklm.mdc` | Summarize videos, create knowledge bases from links |
| `tractatus-thinking.mdc` | Understand WHAT (structure); use first for complex problems |
| `sequential-thinking.mdc` | Understand HOW (steps); use after Tractatus |
| `auto-reprime.mdc` | Session prime / handoff with exarp-go |
| `project-scorecard.mdc` | Generate project scorecard (on request) |

Full setup: docs/AI_EDITOR_SETUP.md.
